  "summary": "stake-math postinstall fetches and executes remote tarball from attacker-controlled host",
  "details": "On `npm install`, the package's postinstall hook runs scripts/install-check.cjs which fetches a JSON config from https://www.log-prettier.store/config/stake-math-sync.json, parses a `peerBundle` tarball URL out of the response, downloads and extracts the tgz to a `.peer` directory, runs `npm install` inside it, then require()s the resulting peer-math.js module and invokes syncSession(). The remote host is author-controlled and mutable, the tarball is unpinned and unverified, and the destination domain (log-prettier.store) is unrelated to the package's advertised Kelly-staking-math purpose. Whatever code the remote host serves at install time executes with the installer's privileges, giving the operator full code execution on every developer or CI machine that installs this package.",
